Press Releases.Title: 2 New Cases of Locally Transmitted Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 3 November 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed 2 new cases of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection. Based on our investigations so far, both reside in dormitories and there are no new cases in the community. 

2         In addition, there are 7 imported cases, who had already been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore. In total, there are 9 new cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore today. 

3         We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight. 

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
3 NOVEMBER 2020
